author: johannadambergk
text: Given is a list of integers. Since the numbers from 1 to 9 are written 01, 02, 03.. and Python doesn't accept leading zeros, how can I remove these zeros, so that the numbers 1 - 9 have no  leading zeros? Example: [322, 65, 18, 03, 78, 4422, 07, 09, 23, 02] to [322, 65, 18, 3, 78, 4422, 7, 9, 23, 2]
title: Removing leading zeros
